<edge source="concept.abstinence" target="concept.food" id="edge.food_drink.concept.abstinence.concerns_food.concept.food">
  <data key="d6">edge.food_drink.concept.abstinence.concerns_food.concept.food</data>
  <data key="d7">concept.abstinence</data>
  <data key="d8">Abstinence</data>
  <data key="d9">virtue</data>
  <data key="d10">concerns_food</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.food</data>
  <data key="d12">Food</data>
  <data key="d13">object</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.concept-abstinence-concerns-food-concept-food-st-ii-ii-q146-a002-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q146.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ssion departs from the good of reason , there is need of a special virtue . Now pleasures of the table are of a nature to withdraw man from the good of reason , both because they are so great, and because food is necessary to man who needs it for the maintenance of life, which he d</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d19">food_drink</data>
  <data key="d20">food | food_drink | temperance_proper</data>
</edge>
<edge source="concept.abstinence" target="concept.virtue" id="edge.food_drink.concept.abstinence.species_of.concept.virtue">
  <data key="d6">edge.food_drink.concept.abstinence.species_of.concept.virtue</data>
  <data key="d7">concept.abstinence</data>
  <data key="d8">Abstinence</data>
  <data key="d9">virtue</data>
  <data key="d10">species_of</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.virtue</data>
  <data key="d12">Virtue</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.concept-abstinence-species-of-concept-virtue-st-ii-ii-q146-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q146.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">tue nor a virtuous act, but something indifferent. Secondly, it may be taken as regulated by reason, and then it signifies either a virtuous habit or a virtuous act. This is the meaning of Peter's words quoted above, where he says that we ought "to join abstinence with knowledge</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d19">food_drink</data>
  <data key="d20">food | food_drink</data>
</edge>
