  <data key="d6">edge.food_drink.concept.abstinence.subjective_part_of.concept.temperance</data>
  <data key="d7">concept.abstinence</data>
  <data key="d8">Abstinence</data>
  <data key="d9">virtue</data>
  <data key="d10">subjective_part_of</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.temperance</data>
  <data key="d12">Temperance</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.concept-abstinence-subjective-part-of-concept-temperance-st-ii-ii-q146-a002-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q146.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ecial motive why a passion departs from the good of reason , there is need of a special virtue . Now pleasures of the table are of a nature to withdraw man from the good of reason , both because they are so great, and because food is necessary to man who needs it for the ma</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d19">food_drink</data>
  <data key="d20">food | food_drink | subjective_part | temperance_proper</data>
</edge>
<edge source="concept.abstinence" target="concept.temperance" id="edge.general_integral.concept.abstinence.subjective_part_of.concept.temperance">
  <data key="d6">edge.general_integral.concept.abstinence.subjective_part_of.concept.temperance</data>
  <data key="d7">concept.abstinence</data>
  <data key="d8">Abstinence</data>
  <data key="d9">virtue</data>
  <data key="d10">subjective_part_of</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.temperance</data>
  <data key="d12">Temperance</data>
  <data key="d13">virtue</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.concept-abstinence-subjective-part-of-concept-temperance-st-ii-ii-q143-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q143.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">. For some are directed to nourishment: and in these as regards meat, there is "abstinence," and as regards drink properly there is "sobriety." Other pleasures are directed to the power of procreation, and in these as regards the principal pleasure of the act itself of</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d19">general_integral</data>
  <data key="d20">food | general_integral | subjective_part | temperance_proper</data>
</edge>
<edge source="concept.adultery_lust" target="concept.lust" id="edge.sexual.concept.adultery_lust.species_of.concept.lust">
  <data key="d6">edge.sexual.concept.adultery_lust.species_of.concept.lust</data>
  <data key="d7">concept.adultery_lust</data>
  <data key="d8">Adultery</data>
  <data key="d9">sin_type</data>
  <data key="d10">species_of</data>
