  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q154.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ty the woman is placed: and if she be under the authority of a husband, it is " adultery ," if under the authority of her father, it is "seduction," in the absence of violence , and "rape" if violence be employed. These species are differentiated on the part of the wo</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d19">sexual</data>
  <data key="d20">sex | sexual</data>
</edge>
