  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q158.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">esire of anger will be sinful , and this is called sinful anger . Secondly, the order of reason in regard to anger may be considered in relation to the mode of being angry , namely that the movement of anger should not be immoderately fierce, neither internally nor externally; and if this cond</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d19">potential_parts</data>
  <data key="d20">meekness_anger | potential_parts</data>
</edge>
