  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q158.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">the sensitive appetite is good in so far as it is regulated by reason, whereas it is evil if it set the order of reason aside. Now the order of reason , in regard to anger , may be considered in relation to two things. First, in relation to the appetible object to which anger tends, and that is revenge.</data>
