  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">an is provoked to inflict a too severe punishment, while it belongs directly to clemency to mitigate punishment, and this might be prevented by excessive anger . Consequently meekness, in so far as it restrains the onslaught of anger , concurs with clemency towards the same effect; yet they</data>
