  <data key="d17">being that he loses the use of reason . On this sense drunkenness denotes not a sin , but a penal defect resulting from a fault. Secondly, drunkenness may denote the act by which a man incurs this defect. This act may cause drunkenness in two ways. On one way, th</data>
