  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Temperance also has a corresponding gift , namely, fear, whereby man is withheld from the pleasures of the flesh, according to Psalm 118:120 : "Pierce Thou my flesh with Thy fear." The gift of fear has for its principal</data>
