  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">concupiscence may be considered from two points of view. First, with regard to things directed to the end, inasmuch as they may be incommensurate and consequently improportionate to the end; secondly, with regard to the end itself, inasmuch as concupiscence turns man away from his due</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
