  <data key="d14">ann.concept-gluttony-excess-opposed-to-concept-abstinence-st-ii-ii-q148-a001-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q148.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Gluttony denotes, not any desire of eating and drinking, but an inordinate desire. Now desire is said to be inordinate through leaving the order of reason , wherein the good of moral virtue consists: and a thing is said to be a sin through being contrary to vir</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d19">food_drink</data>
  <data key="d20">food | food_drink</data>
</edge>
