  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">The sin of incontinence may be considered in two ways. First, on the part of the passion which occasions the downfall of reason. In this way incontinence of desire is worse than incontinence of anger , because the movement of desire is more inordinate than the</data>
