  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">nce is, as we have said in reference to continence ( II-II:155:2 ). On this way incontinence is a sin for two reasons: first, because the incontinent man goes astray from that which is in accord with reason; secondly, because he plunges into shameful pleasures. Hence the Philosoph</data>
