  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q143.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ment is that of anger , which tends towards revenge, and this is restrained by "meekness" or "mildness." With regard to bodily movements and actions, moderation and restraint is the effect of "modesty," which, according to Andronicus, has three parts. The first of the</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
