  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( Article 1 ; II-II:109:2 ; 123, 12 ), the good of moral virtue consists chiefly in the order of reason: because " man's good is to be in accord with reason," as Dionysius asserts (Div. Nom. iv). Now the principal order of reason is that by which it directs certain things towards th</data>
