  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( 123, 11 ; II-II:61:3 ), a principal or cardinal virtue is so called because it has a foremost claim to praise on account of one of those things that are requisite for the notion of virtue in general. Now moderation, which is requisite</data>
